parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the transmission and AutoStop feature can cause the vehicle to hesitate or lose power while driving, leading to potential accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates or loses power while driving
the engine revs up
the RPM reaches high levels
the gears do not shift correctly
the vehicle moves slowly
and the AutoStop feature fails to engage or disengage properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unusual engine noise and whistling sound can be a sign of a more serious underlying issue, potentially affecting the vehicle's performance and safety.
symptoms: The engine makes a squeaking noise when turned off
a whistling sound when accelerating or changing gears
and a loud knocking noise when the vehicle is turned off.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the infotainment system can cause distractions while driving, potentially leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The screen goes black with red writing
the GPS talks through the screen
and the screen freezes with a variation of colors
disabling the use of the infotainment system.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch and transmission system can cause the vehicle to become stuck in gear, leading to potential accidents or strandings.
symptoms: The vehicle locks up and cannot move
the clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
and the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Safety Restraint System can lead to a risk of accidents or injuries, as the airbag system may not deploy properly in the event of a crash.
symptoms: Alert signal or warning light on the dashboard
airbag light indicates "off"
safety restraint system panel defective.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump/injection system can cause the engine to malfunction, leading to a loss of power, stalling, or even engine failure, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Check engine light
engine failure
defective fuel pump/injection system.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause various systems in the vehicle to malfunction, leading to a risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Service Instrument Cluster failure
sunroof malfunction
loud noise like knocking coming from the front of the vehicle after turning off the car.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission/gearbox can cause the vehicle to hesitate, jerk, or lose power, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Gears not shifting correctly
RPM jumping up
vehicle hesitating
engine accelerating unevenly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Issues with vehicle software updates can cause various systems in the vehicle to malfunction, leading to a risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Service Instrument Cluster failure
parts on backorder
software update not correcting the problem.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Pedal Issues with Intermittent Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent failure of the brake pedal can cause the vehicle to fail to stop immediately, leading to potential accidents or near-misses, which can result in serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal requires excessive force to depress
the vehicle takes longer to stop than usual
the engine revs abnormally as if the vehicle is accelerating
the brake pedal feels spongy or soft
the vehicle fails to stop immediately.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump control module can cause the vehicle to stall or die, leading to a loss of power and control, which can increase the risk of accidents, especially in busy intersections.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or dies
unable to start
unable to shift into neutral
loss of power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The ongoing engine and powertrain issues can cause the vehicle to malfunction, leading to a loss of control, accidents, and safety risks to drivers and passengers.
symptoms: Squeaking sounds coming from the engine when manually turning the car off
coolant smell coming from the engine
loud whistling sound when accelerating in speed
engine squeaking/squealing sounds.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the turbocharger can cause the engine to malfunction, leading to a loss of power, accidents, and safety risks to drivers and passengers.
symptoms: Squeaking sounds coming from the engine
coolant smell coming from the engine
loud whistling sound when accelerating in speed.
